cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.CC, cs.CG. 

The paper deals with communication cost of computing functions in a network/graph, which involves topics such as distributed computing, graph algorithms, and network information theory. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.IT (Information Theory), and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) are likely sub-categories. The paper also uses tools from the theory of tree embeddings and multiway cuts, which are related to computational geometry and graph theory, respectively, suggesting cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) as possible sub-categories as well.
